1.2 HOW IT REDUCES LATENCY & IMPROVES PERFORMANCE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
▸ Simple
  By using "Caching." If the proxy already has the image you want, it gives it
  to you instantly without traveling across the ocean to the real server.

▸ Performance Deep-Dive (Advanced)
  - Cache Hits/Misses: A "Hit" means data was found locally (fast). A "Miss"
    means the proxy had to go fetch it (slower).
  - DNS Caching: The proxy remembers the IP for "facebook.com", saving the
    time needed for a DNS lookup.
  - Bandwidth Saving: Since it serves local copies, the company's main
    internet line isn't clogged with repetitive requests.


