2.2 ADVANCED REVERSE PROXY CONCEPTS
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────━━━━━━━━━━━
▸ Global Server Load Balancing (GSLB)
  Instead of one data center, the proxy routes you to the nearest data center
  (e.g., if you are in London, it sends you to the UK server).

▸ Health Checks
  The Reverse Proxy constantly "pings" the backend servers. If Server B dies,
  the proxy automatically stops sending traffic there and redirects to A and C.

▸ Sticky Sessions (Session Persistence)
  Ensures a user stays on the SAME backend server for their whole session
  (important for shopping carts if the data isn't shared across servers).

▸ Blue-Green / Canary Deployments
  The proxy can send 95% of users to the "Old" version and 5% to the "New"
  version to test for bugs before a full launch.


