SECTION 4 ◆ SECURITY & PERFORMANCE DEEP DIVE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

4.1 SSL TERMINATION (Advanced)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Encryption is "expensive" (takes a lot of CPU juice).
  - Without Proxy: Server A must decrypt every single packet.
  - With Proxy: The Proxy does the decryption. It talks to Server A via
    plain HTTP (over a secure internal network). This makes Server A much faster.

4.2 WEB APPLICATION FIREWALL (WAF)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  The Reverse Proxy can inspect requests for "SQL Injection" or "Cross-Site
  Scripting" (XSS). It blocks the bad request BEFORE it even touches your
  database or code.

4.3 CONTENT CACHING (The Speed Secret)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  - Static Content: The proxy stores images, CSS, and JS files.
  - Dynamic Content: The proxy can even store API results for a few seconds.
  Result: The backend server does ZERO work for 90% of requests.

